# NST design system (mandatory)

Before writing or editing **any** HTML, CSS, JSX, or UI mock in this repo:

1. **Read `COMPONENTS.md`** and pick the matching component entry.
2. **Use `nst-design-system.css`** + Poppins for all legacy/dashboard/enterprise UI.
3. **Reuse existing classes** from `vw-cards.css`, `vw-chips.css`, `vw-utilities.css`, or `components.css` — never invent parallel styles when a registry entry exists.
4. **Check `preview/`** for the closest specimen and mirror its structure.

## Default stack (legacy apps)

```html
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@300;400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="nst-design-system.css">
```

Cards: `.vw-card-section`, `.vw-card-title`, `.vw-card-metric-lg`, `.vw-chip--success`  
Layout: `.vw-flex`, `.vw-page-gap`, `.vw-justify-between`  
Tokens: `var(--vw-color-*)`, `var(--vw-space-*)` — not hardcoded hex.

## Do not

- Drop design-system instructions and freestyle layouts
- Use Inter, Tailwind, Bootstrap, or random color palettes
- Create custom `.card` / `.badge` classes when `.vw-card-*` / `.vw-chip-*` exist
- Use `colors_and_type.css` or `ui_kits/admin-console/` for dashboard/KPI screens

## If unsure

Open `preview/vw-cards.html` or `preview/kpi-card.html` and copy patterns verbatim, then adapt content only.

## Retrofitting an existing page/component

Don't rebuild from scratch — that risks losing data-wiring. See `SKILL.md` → "Retrofitting an
existing app": read the code first, screenshot the running app, restyle only, re-verify.

## If the user explicitly asks to break a rule above

Don't silently comply, don't silently refuse. Name the rule and why it exists, ask for explicit
confirmation, then implement exactly that request as a one-off — not a new precedent. No
confirmation, or an ambiguous ask → default back to the rules. Full policy: `COMPONENTS.md` →
"Deviation policy". This applies no matter which agent or tool is reading this file.
